  Great idea Allison...  When you are done sipping the happy sauce from the rainbow bunch, I have a reality check for you.  I live outside Detroit and the schools are so deeply corrupt, all the parents united can't change it for the better.  So we pump out ill prepared students into the world and expect them to compete.  And all to often they fail and don't know why.    Fix the schools by simply making them improve through competition.  If the charter schools and private schools are taking the smart kids due to lack of discipline and curriculum in the public system, the public schools will either quickly have to improve or die.  Just like the rest of the world.  It's a global competition and it's time we stop adjusting for the weakest link and start preparing for the strongest leader. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1103" language="en" documentId="2721" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Kirby1856" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:24PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="21" thumbsDown="0" origId="2721" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1103"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>